<section sectnbr = "3A">
<servcat sctnbr = "03" scnbr = "01">
<configtype typenbr = "1">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B3116005" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Drive Intermediate Shaft Assembly Removal and Installation
</title>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B3116005001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Drain transaxle oil (M/T model) or A/T fluid (A/T model).
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
M/T model: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B5206002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
A/T model: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B5106003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove right side front drive shaft assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B3116003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove intermediate support bolts (1) and drive intermediate shaft assembly (2) from transaxle.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Be careful not to damage differential side oil seal while removing the drive intermediate shaft.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<figure>
<title>
M/T model
</title>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B311004.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "56.038mm" ver = "01" gw = "185" gh = "142"/>
</figure>
<figure>
<title>
A/T model
</title>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B311005.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "56.050mm" ver = "01" gw = "185" gh = "142"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B3116005002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Be careful not to damage differential side oil seal while installing the drive intermediate shaft.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<ptxt>
Reverse removal procedure, noting the following points:
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Use new circlip.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Tighten intermediate support bolts (1) in numerical order as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Temporarily tighten intermediate support bolts in numerical order (“1” – “3”).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Tighten intermediate support bolts to specified torque in the same manner as in Step 1).
</ptxt>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T3A102">
<t-part>
Intermediate support bolt
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
55
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
5.6
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
40.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
<figure>
<title>
M/T model
</title>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B311006.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "56.038mm" ver = "01" gw = "185" gh = "142"/>
</figure>
<figure>
<title>
A/T model
</title>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B311007.jpg" width = "88.000mm" height = "56.038mm" ver = "01" gw = "185" gh = "142"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
